    ('CSCI-H 200', 'INTRODUCTION TO COMPUTERS AND PROGRAMMING, HONORS', '9053', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 3:55 PM–5:10 PM', 'GY 4069', 'Mehmet Dalkilic', 0, 'Lecture', 'Lecture', '4', 'GEOLOGICAL SCIENCES', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Honors version of CSCI-C 200. This course is an introduction, broadly, to algorithmic thinking and, specifically, to programming. It teaches the basics of programming using real world applications in natural, physical and social sciences. Students will develop ability to program by identifying problems in real world and then creating a program that solves the problem.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
