    ('EALC-E 100', 'EAST ASIA: AN INTRODUCTION', '8414', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 9:10 AM–10:00 AM', 'MY 130', 'Scott O''Bryan', 9, 'Lecture', 'Lecture', '3', 'MYERS HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Basic introduction to China, Japan, and Korea. Intended to help students understand the unique character of each of these cultures within the general framework of East Asian civilization, comprehend the historical importance of the three countries, and appreciate the crucial role they play in the world today.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd A&H credit
